body:
Related: #22303

This PR proposes a change to the [`PubSubHook.publish`](https://airflow.apache.org/docs/apache-airflow-providers-google/stable/_api/airflow/providers/google/cloud/hooks/pubsub/index.html#airflow.providers.google.cloud.hooks.pubsub.PubSubHook.publish) method. I updated the method signature to include support for string-type message data. Previously, the operator only allowed byte-type message data, which made it complicated for users to use templated message data. For example, the following would not work.

```py
with DAG(...):
    @task
    def create_messages():
        return json.dumps([{"data": "hello world"}])

    publish_messages = PubSubPublishMessageOperator(
        task_id="publish_messages",
        project="test",
        topic="test",
        messages="{{ ti.xcom_pull('create_messages') }}"
    )

    create_messages() >> publish_messages
```

Since bytes-type data is not JSON serializable, the only way to make the above example work is to set [`render_template_as_native_obj=True`](https://airflow.apache.org/docs/apache-airflow/stable/core-concepts/operators.html#rendering-fields-as-native-python-objects) alongside a custom jinja2 filter to convert the xcom value to bytes.

```py
def to_bytes(value):
    return value.encode("utf-8")

with DAG(..., render_template_as_native_obj=True, user_defined_filters={"to_bytes": to_bytes}):
    @task
    def create_messages():
        return json.dumps([{"data": "hello world"}])

    publish_messages = PubSubPublishMessageOperator(
        task_id="publish_messages",
        project="test",
        topic="test",
        messages="{{ ti.xcom_pull('create_messages') | to_bytes }}"
    )

    create_messages() >> publish_messages
```

With this change, users can now easily use templated message data in string format, making the operator more versatile and user-friendly. The changes are backward compatible, so existing operators can continue to use bytes-type message data.
